Hungary Forint Basic Trend Points to More Gains, Patai Says

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-09-30T08:40:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/hungary-forint-basic-trend-points-to-more-gains-patai-says.html
The Hungarian forint is set to
strengthen in the long-term, Mihaly Patai, head of the Hungarian
Banking Association said.  “The basic trend of the forint points toward more gains
going forward,” Patai said at a conference in Budapest today.
Exhcange rate “swings” are likely to take place, with
volatility caused primarily by global economic events, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edith Balazs at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net  